{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775857171418,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d7955fbd8001hNOhAYdd4ALfmT","messageID":"msg_d7955ee1500137TrPFEaU04aaa","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857244740,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d795719e2001x8kFHhG3Sei4oT","messageID":"msg_d7955ee1500137TrPFEaU04aaa","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-6296528fe2224f6aba461b2af1802f20","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-013: Redis Storage Implementation\n\nModule: `pkg/store`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: M\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement Redis-backed session storage for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Store interface\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface with methods for sandbox lifecycle management.\n\n### Scenario: Interface definition\n\n- **GIVEN** package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n- **WHEN** the package is compiled\n- **THEN** interface `Store` is defined with methods:\n  - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n  - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n  - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n  - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n  - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error`\n  - `Close() error`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Not found error\n\nThe system SHALL export `ErrNotFound` for absent session lookups.\n\n### Scenario: ErrNotFound exported\n\n- **GIVEN** the store package\n- **WHEN** imported by consumers\n- **THEN** `var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")` is accessible\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Redis client initialization\n\nThe system SHALL initialize Redis client from environment variables.\n\n### Scenario: Redis client from env\n\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set to `localhost:6379`\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is set to `secret`\n- **WHEN** `makeRedisOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** returned `*redisv9.Options` has `Addr: \"localhost:6379\"` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n\n### Scenario: Password optional when disabled\n\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is `\"false\"`\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization succeeds with empty password\n\n### Scenario: Password required by default\n\n- **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is unset\n- **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating password required\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Key naming convention\n\nThe system SHALL use prefix `session:` for session keys.\n\n### Scenario: Session key format\n\n- **GIVEN** session ID `abc123`\n- **WHEN** `sessionKey(id)` is computed\n- **THEN** result is `\"session:abc123\"`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Ping connectivity\n\nThe system SHALL verify Redis connectivity via PING command.\n\n### Scenario: Ping returns PONG\n\n- **GIVEN** a connected Redis client\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** Redis PING command is issued\n- **AND** return is `nil` if response equals `\"PONG\"`\n\n### Scenario: Ping fails on error\n\n- **GIVEN** Redis is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned from the Redis client\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Get sandbox by session ID\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve sandbox JSON by session key.\n\n### Scenario: Get existing session\n\n- **GIVEN** key `session:abc` exists with valid JSON\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called\n- **THEN** Redis `GET session:abc` is issued\n- **AND** returned `*types.SandboxInfo` is unmarshaled from JSON\n\n### Scenario: Get missing session\n\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:xyz`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\")` is called\n- **THEN** Redis returns `redis.Nil` error\n- **AND** method returns `nil, ErrNotFound`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Store sandbox atomically\n\nThe system SHALL create session with expiry and activity indexes in one pipeline.\n\n### Scenario: Store new sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with `SessionID: \"s1\"`, `ExpiresAt: t`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** pipeline executes:\n  - `SETNX session:s1 <json>` (set if not exists)\n  - `ZADD session:expiry <t.Unix()> s1`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> s1`\n- **AND** returns `nil` on success\n\n### Scenario: Reject nil sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** `sandbox` is `nil`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating sandbox is nil\n\n### Scenario: Reject zero expiry\n\n- **GIVEN** sandbox with `ExpiresAt: time.Time{}` (zero value)\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned indicating invalid expiry\n\n### Scenario: Reject duplicate session\n\n- **GIVEN** key `session:s1` already exists\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called for same session ID\n- **THEN** SETNX returns `false`\n- **AND** error indicates session already exists\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Update sandbox\n\nThe system SHALL update session JSON only, preserving indexes.\n\n### Scenario: Update existing session\n\n- **GIVEN** key `session:s1` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** Redis `SET session:s1 <json> XX` is issued (XX = only if exists)\n- **AND** returns `nil` on success\n\n### Scenario: Update missing session\n\n- **GIVEN** key `session:s1` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** SET with XX returns `false`\n- **AND** error indicates key does not exist\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Delete sandbox\n\nThe system SHALL remove session key and index entries atomically.\n\n### Scenario: Delete existing session\n\n- **GIVEN** session `s1` exists with ZSET entries\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` is called\n- **THEN** pipeline executes:\n  - `DEL session:s1`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry s1`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity s1`\n- **AND** returns `nil`\n\n### Scenario: Delete missing session\n\n- **GIVEN** session `s1` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\")` is called\n- **THEN** pipeline still executes DEL and ZREM\n- **AND** returns `nil` (no error for missing)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: List expired sandboxes\n\nThe system SHALL query expiry index and load corresponding sessions.\n\n### Scenario: List with valid limit\n\n- **GIVEN** ZSET `session:expiry` contains entries\n- **AND** `before` = `2025-01-01T00:00:00Z`\n- **AND** `limit` = 10\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf <before.Unix()> LIMIT 0 10` is issued\n- **AND** for each session ID returned, pipeline GETs `session:{id}`\n- **AND** returns slice of `*types.SandboxInfo`\n\n### Scenario: Skip orphan ZSET entries\n\n- **GIVEN** session ID `orphan1` in `session:expiry` ZSET\n- **AND** no corresponding `session:orphan1` key\n- **WHEN** listing expired sessions\n- **THEN** orphan entry is skipped without error\n- **AND** other valid sessions are returned\n\n### Scenario: Zero limit returns nil\n\n- **GIVEN** `limit` <= 0\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** returns `nil, nil` without Redis calls\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: List inactive sandboxes\n\nThe system SHALL query last-activity index.\n\n### Scenario: List by activity\n\n- **GIVEN** ZSET `session:last_activity` contains entries\n- **AND** `before` and `limit` are valid\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf <before.Unix()> LIMIT 0 limit` is issued\n- **AND** session data is loaded via pipeline GETs\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Update session last activity\n\nThe system SHALL update activity timestamp with existence check.\n\n### Scenario: Update activity for existing session\n\n- **GIVEN** key `session:s1` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called with non-zero `at`\n- **THEN** `ZADD session:last_activity <at.Unix()> s1` is issued\n- **AND** returns `nil`\n\n### Scenario: Use current time when at is zero\n\n- **GIVEN** key `session:s1` exists\n- **AND** `at` is zero `time.Time{}`\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** `time.Now()` is used for the score\n\n### Scenario: Reject empty session ID\n\n- **GIVEN** `sessionID` is empty string\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** error indicates session ID is empty\n\n### Scenario: Reject missing session\n\n- **GIVEN** key `session:s1` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Close connection\n\nThe system SHALL close Redis client gracefully.\n\n### Scenario: Close succeeds\n\n- **GIVEN** a connected Redis client\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** `redis.Client.Close()` is invoked\n- **AND** returns `nil`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Singleton access\n\nThe system SHALL provide singleton `Storage()` with lazy initialization.\n\n### Scenario: Singleton initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** package-level `sync.Once` and `Store` variable\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called first time\n- **THEN** `initStore` runs exactly once\n- **AND** Redis client is created and returned\n\n### Scenario: Concurrent access\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently\n- **WHEN** initialization is in progress\n- **THEN** all wait for completion\n- **AND** same `Store` instance is returned\n\n### Scenario: Init failure is fatal\n\n- **GIVEN** Redis connection fails\n- **WHEN** `initStore` returns error\n- **THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is called with error message\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Provider type constants\n\nThe system SHALL define store type constants.\n\n### Scenario: Redis store type constant\n\n- **GIVEN** the store package\n- **WHEN** constants are defined\n- **THEN** `redisStoreType = \"redis\"` and `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"` are available\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Store type selection\n\nThe system SHALL select backend based on `STORE_TYPE` environment variable.\n\n### Scenario: Default to redis\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n- **WHEN** `initStore` runs\n- **THEN** Redis implementation is selected\n\n### Scenario: Explicit redis\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE = \"redis\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `initStore` runs\n- **THEN** Redis implementation is selected\n\n### Scenario: Explicit valkey\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE = \"valkey\"` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `initStore` runs\n- **THEN** Valkey implementation is selected\n\n### Scenario: Invalid store type\n\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE = \"unknown\"`\n- **WHEN** `initStore` runs\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Redis struct fields\n\nThe system SHALL define `redisStore` struct with required fields.\n\n### Scenario: Redis struct definition\n\n- **GIVEN** implementation file `store_redis.go`\n- **WHEN** compiled\n- **THEN** struct `redisStore` contains:\n  - `cli *redisv9.Client`\n  - `sessionPrefix string` (value: `\"session:\"`)\n  - `expiryIndexKey string` (value: `\"session:expiry\"`)\n  - `lastActivityIndexKey string` (value: `\"session:last_activity\"`)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: SandboxInfo JSON marshaling\n\nThe system SHALL marshal/unmarshal `types.SandboxInfo` as JSON.\n\n### Scenario: JSON fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `types.SandboxInfo` struct\n- **WHEN** marshaled to JSON\n- **THEN** fields map to:\n  - `kind` → `Kind`\n  - `sandboxId` → `SandboxID`\n  - `sandboxNamespace` → `SandboxNamespace`\n  - `name` → `Name`\n  - `entryPoints` → `EntryPoints`\n  - `sessionId` → `SessionID`\n  - `createdAt` → `CreatedAt`\n  - `expiresAt` → `ExpiresAt`\n  - `status` → `Status`\n\n---\n\n## File structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store.go           # Interface, ErrNotFound, singleton\n├── store_redis.go     # Redis implementation\n├── store_valkey.go    # Valkey implementation\n└── store_test.go      # Integration tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n- `k8s.io/klog/v2`"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775857244733,"end":1775857244737}}}}
