{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775857248783,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d795729f8001K4yulLkoztmMSv","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79571a6a001x4jKfc54UGR3rv","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":26156,"input":3388,"output":77,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":22691}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775857251772,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d795735b8001SdcJ1gYuwP4ubC","messageID":"msg_d79572a25001i15I4y4V3TnReq","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857253005,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d79573a62001fA4gRaieC2jmCt","messageID":"msg_d79572a25001i15I4y4V3TnReq","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c1879c941e734d12ba93acd55a29d358","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: Module: `pkg/router`\n4: Language: Go\n5: Size: M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Router session management subsystem, providing session lifecycle management, sandbox routing, reverse proxy, JWT authentication, unified error handling, and middleware support for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocation requests.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### REQ-001: SessionManager Interface\n18: \n19: **GIVEN** the Router needs to manage sessions for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter  \n20: **WHEN** handling session-based routing requests  \n21: **THEN** SessionManager interface shall be properly defined with GetSandboxBySession method\n22: \n23: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n24: \n25: ```go\n26: // Scenario 1: SessionManager interface definition\n27: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n28: WHEN reading the SessionManager interface\n29: THEN it SHALL define GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n30: \n31: // Scenario 2: SessionManager implementation\n32: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\n33: WHEN reading the sessionManager struct\n34: THEN it SHALL contain fields: storeClient Store, workloadMgrAddr string, httpClient *http.Client\n35: \n36: // Scenario 3: NewSessionManager constructor\n37: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\n38: WHEN calling NewSessionManager(storeClient Store)\n39: THEN it SHALL read WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL from environment variable\n40: AND it SHALL return error if WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL is not set\n41: AND it SHALL configure HTTP client with 2 minute timeout and HTTP2 transport\n42: \n43: // Scenario 4: NewSessionManager environment requirement\n44: GIVEN WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable not set\n45: WHEN calling NewSessionManager(storeClient)\n46: THEN it SHALL return error with message \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable is required\"\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### REQ-002: GetSandboxBySession Method\n52: \n53: **GIVEN** a session needs to be looked up or created  \n54: **WHEN** invoking GetSandboxBySession  \n55: **THEN** the method shall return existing sandbox or create a new one\n56: \n57: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: // Scenario 1: Existing session lookup\n61: GIVEN a sessionManager with Store containing session \"existing-session\"\n62: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"existing-session\", \"default\", \"test\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n63: THEN it SHALL call storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"existing-session\")\n64: AND it SHALL return the existing SandboxInfo\n65: \n66: // Scenario 2: Empty sessionID creates new sandbox\n67: GIVEN a sessionManager with empty sessionID parameter\n68: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"\", \"default\", \"test-runtime\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n69: THEN it SHALL call createSandbox to create new sandbox\n70: AND it SHALL NOT call storeClient.GetSandboxBySessionID\n71: \n72: // Scenario 3: Session not found error\n73: GIVEN a sessionManager with Store returning error for session \"nonexistent\"\n74: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"nonexistent\", \"default\", \"test\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n75: THEN it SHALL return SessionNotFoundError with SessionID field set\n76: \n77: // Scenario 4: Namespace and name passed to createSandbox\n78: GIVEN a sessionManager creating new sandbox\n79: WHEN calling GetSandboxBySession(ctx, \"\", \"my-namespace\", \"my-runtime\", \"AgentRuntime\")\n80: THEN createSandbox SHALL receive namespace=\"my-namespace\", name=\"my-runtime\", kind=\"AgentRuntime\"\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ### REQ-003: CreateSandbox Method\n86: \n87: **GIVEN** a new sandbox needs to be created via WorkloadManager  \n88: **WHEN** calling createSandbox  \n89: **THEN** it shall send HTTP POST request to WorkloadManager and store the result\n90: \n91: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n92: \n93: ```go\n94: // Scenario 1: AgentRuntime endpoint selection\n95: GIVEN createSandbox with kind \"AgentRuntime\"\n96: WHEN building the HTTP request endpoint\n97: THEN endpoint SHALL be workloadMgrAddr + \"/v1/agent-runtime\"\n98: \n99: // Scenario 2: CodeInterpreter endpoint selection\n100: GIVEN createSandbox with kind \"CodeInterpreter\"\n101: WHEN building the HTTP request endpoint\n102: THEN endpoint SHALL be workloadMgrAddr + \"/v1/code-interpreter\"\n103: \n104: // Scenario 3: Unsupported kind error\n105: GIVEN createSandbox with kind \"UnsupportedKind\"\n106: WHEN executing the method\n107: THEN it SHALL return error \"unsupported kind: UnsupportedKind\"\n108: \n109: // Scenario 4: Request body marshaling\n110: GIVEN createSandbox called\n111: WHEN building the HTTP request body\n112: THEN body SHALL be JSON marshaled CreateSandboxRequest{Kind, Name, Namespace}\n113: \n114: // Scenario 5: Request validation\n115: GIVEN CreateSandboxRequest with invalid parameters\n116: WHEN calling Validate()\n117: THEN it SHALL return error if Kind is not AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n118: AND it SHALL return error if Namespace is empty\n119: AND it SHALL return error if Name is empty\n120: \n121: // Scenario 6: WorkloadManager HTTP error\n122: GIVEN WorkloadManager returning HTTP 500\n123: WHEN createSandbox processes response\n124: THEN it SHALL return WorkloadManagerError with StatusCode 500\n125: \n126: // Scenario 7: Empty sessionId in response\n127: GIVEN WorkloadManager returning response with empty sessionId\n128: WHEN createSandbox processes response\n129: THEN it SHALL return error \"empty sessionId in response\"\n130: \n131: // Scenario 8: Sandbox stored in Store\n132: GIVEN successful WorkloadManager response\n133: WHEN createSandbox processes response\n134: THEN it SHALL call storeClient.StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n135: AND sandbox SHALL have Kind, SandboxID, SandboxNamespace, SandboxName, Name, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, EntryPoints fields\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### REQ-004: Store Interface\n141: \n142: **GIVEN** the Router needs to persist and retrieve session data  \n143: **WHEN** managing session storage  \n144: **THEN** Store interface shall be properly defined\n145: \n146: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n147: \n148: ```go\n149: // Scenario 1: Store interface definition\n150: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n151: WHEN reading the Store interface\n152: THEN it SHALL define GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n153: AND it SHALL define StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n154: AND it SHALL define UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n155: \n156: // Scenario 2: Store used by SessionManager\n157: GIVEN sessionManager struct\n158: WHEN reading the implementation\n159: THEN storeClient field SHALL be of type Store\n160: \n161: // Scenario 3: Store used by Server\n162: GIVEN Server struct\n163: WHEN reading the implementation\n164: THEN storeClient field SHALL be of type Store\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ---\n168: \n169: ### REQ-005: Service Account Token\n170: \n171: **GIVEN** Router needs to authenticate with WorkloadManager  \n172: **WHEN** sending requests to WorkloadManager  \n173: **THEN** it shall use Kubernetes service account token\n174: \n175: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n176: \n177: ```go\n178: // Scenario 1: readServiceAccountToken function\n179: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager.go\n180: WHEN reading readServiceAccountToken function\n181: THEN it SHALL read from \"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\"\n182: AND it SHALL return trimmed token string\n183: \n184: // Scenario 2: Token added to request header\n185: GIVEN createSandbox with valid service account token\n186: WHEN building HTTP request\n187: THEN Authorization header SHALL be \"Bearer \" + saToken\n188: \n189: // Scenario 3: Token read error handled gracefully\n190: GIVEN service account token file not existing\n191: WHEN readServiceAccountToken returns error\n192: THEN request SHALL proceed without Authorization header\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ### REQ-006: Router Server Configuration\n198: \n199: **GIVEN** Router needs configurable HTTP server  \n200: **WHEN** setting up the server  \n201: **THEN** Config struct shall support all necessary options\n202: \n203: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n204: \n205: ```go\n206: // Scenario 1: Config struct definition\n207: GIVEN pkg/router/config.go\n208: WHEN reading the Config struct\n209: THEN it SHALL contain fields: Port string, EnableTLS bool, TLSCert string, TLSKey string, MaxConcurrentRequests int, Debug bool\n210: \n211: // Scenario 2: DefaultConfig function\n212: GIVEN pkg/router/config.go\n213: WHEN calling DefaultConfig()\n214: THEN it SHALL return Config with Port \":8080\", EnableTLS false, MaxConcurrentRequests 1000, Debug false\n215: \n216: // Scenario 3: Server constructor with nil config\n217: GIVEN NewServer called with nil config\n218: WHEN constructing Server\n219: THEN DefaultConfig SHALL be used\n220: \n221: // Scenario 4: MaxConcurrentRequests default\n222: GIVEN Config with MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0\n223: WHEN constructing Server\n224: THEN MaxConcurrentRequests SHALL be set to 1000\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### REQ-007: Router Server Structure\n230: \n231: **GIVEN** Router needs HTTP server with Gin framework  \n232: **WHEN** constructing the Server  \n233: **THEN** Server struct shall contain all necessary components\n234: \n235: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // Scenario 1: Server struct definition\n239: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n240: WHEN reading the Server struct\n241: THEN it SHALL contain fields: config *Config, engine *gin.Engine, httpServer *http.Server, sessionManager SessionManager, storeClient Store, httpTransport *http.Transport, jwtManager *JWTManager, logger Logger\n242: \n243: // Scenario 2: Server constructor\n244: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n245: WHEN calling NewServer(config, sessionManager, storeClient, jwtManager, logger)\n246: THEN it SHALL return *Server with all fields initialized\n247: AND gin.Engine SHALL be created with gin.New()\n248: AND http.Server SHALL have ReadTimeout 30s, IdleTimeout 90s\n249: \n250: // Scenario 3: Gin mode configuration\n251: GIVEN Config with Debug false\n252: WHEN constructing Server\n253: THEN gin.SetMode SHALL be gin.ReleaseMode\n254: \n255: // Scenario 4: Gin mode with Debug true\n256: GIVEN Config with Debug true\n257: WHEN constructing Server\n258: THEN gin.SetMode SHALL be gin.DebugMode\n259: \n260: // Scenario 5: registerRoutes called\n261: GIVEN NewServer constructing Server\n262: WHEN initialization completes\n263: THEN registerRoutes SHALL be called\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ---\n267: \n268: ### REQ-008: Router Route Registration\n269: \n270: **GIVEN** Router needs RESTful API endpoints  \n271: **WHEN** registering routes  \n272: **THEN** all endpoints shall be properly registered with middleware\n273: \n274: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n275: \n276: ```go\n277: // Scenario 1: Health endpoints registered\n278: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n279: WHEN reading route registration\n280: THEN /health/live endpoint SHALL be registered with GET method\n281: AND /health/ready endpoint SHALL be registered with GET method\n282: \n283: // Scenario 2: AgentRuntime invocation endpoints\n284: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n285: WHEN reading route registration\n286: THEN /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path SHALL be registered with GET and POST methods\n287: \n288: // Scenario 3: CodeInterpreter invocation endpoints\n289: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n290: WHEN reading route registration\n291: THEN /v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path SHALL be registered with GET and POST methods\n292: \n293: // Scenario 4: Middleware applied to v1 group\n294: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go registerRoutes method\n295: WHEN reading v1 route group\n296: THEN concurrencyLimitMiddleware SHALL be applied\n297: AND loggingMiddleware SHALL be applied if logger is not nil\n298: AND recoveryMiddleware SHALL be applied if logger is not nil\n299: ```\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ### REQ-009: Health Endpoints\n304: \n305: **GIVEN** Kubernetes needs liveness and readiness probes  \n306: **WHEN** implementing health endpoints  \n307: **THEN** proper health responses shall be returned\n308: \n309: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n310: \n311: ```go\n312: // Scenario 1: handleHealthLive endpoint\n313: GIVEN GET request to /health/live\n314: WHEN handler executes\n315: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON {\"status\": \"alive\"}\n316: \n317: // Scenario 2: handleHealthReady with SessionManager\n318: GIVEN GET request to /health/ready with valid SessionManager\n319: WHEN handler executes\n320: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 200 with JSON {\"status\": \"ready\"}\n321: \n322: // Scenario 3: handleHealthReady without SessionManager\n323: GIVEN GET request to /health/ready with nil SessionManager\n324: WHEN handler executes\n325: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 503 with JSON {\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ### REQ-010: Invoke Handler\n331: \n332: **GIVEN** invocation requests need to be routed to sandbox  \n333: **WHEN** handling AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter invocation  \n334: **THEN** request shall be proxied to the correct sandbox endpoint\n335: \n336: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n337: \n338: ```go\n339: // Scenario 1: handleAgentInvoke delegates to handleInvoke\n340: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n341: WHEN reading handleAgentInvoke method\n342: THEN it SHALL call handleInvoke(c, types.AgentRuntimeKind)\n343: \n344: // Scenario 2: handleCodeInterpreterInvoke delegates\n345: GIVEN pkg/router/server.go\n346: WHEN reading handleCodeInterpreterInvoke method\n347: THEN it SHALL call handleInvoke(c, types.CodeInterpreterKind)\n348: \n349: // Scenario 3: SessionID from header\n350: GIVEN invocation request\n351: WHEN handleInvoke reads sessionID\n352: THEN it SHALL read from \"x-agentcube-session-id\" header\n353: \n354: // Scenario 4: Parameters extracted from URL\n355: GIVEN invocation request to /v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-runtime/invocations/api/test\n356: WHEN handleInvoke processes request\n357: THEN namespace SHALL be \"default\"\n358: AND name SHALL be \"my-runtime\"\n359: AND invocationPath SHALL be \"/api/test\"\n360: \n361: // Scenario 5: GetSandboxBySession called\n362: GIVEN handleInvoke with valid parameters\n363: WHEN processing request\n364: THEN sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession SHALL be called with ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind\n365: \n366: // Scenario 6: No entry point error\n367: GIVEN sandbox with empty EntryPoints\n368: WHEN handleInvoke processes request\n369: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 404 with JSON {\"error\": \"no entry point configured\", \"code\": \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\"}\n370: \n371: // Scenario 7: UpdateSessionLastActivity before proxy\n372: GIVEN successful sandbox lookup\n373: WHEN before proxying request\n374: THEN storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity SHALL be called with current time\n375: \n376: // Scenario 8: Entry point selection\n377: GIVEN sandbox with multiple entry points\n378: WHEN selecting entry point\n379: THEN selectEntryPoint SHALL be called with entryPoints and invocationPath\n380: ```\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ### REQ-011: Entry Point Selection\n385: \n386: **GIVEN** sandbox has multiple entry points  \n387: **WHEN** routing request to entry point  \n388: **THEN** correct entry point shall be selected based on path prefix\n389: \n390: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n391: \n392: ```go\n393: // Scenario 1: selectEntryPoint matching path\n394: GIVEN entry points [{Path: \"/api\"}, {Path: \"/execute\"}] and invocationPath \"/api/v1/resource\"\n395: WHEN calling selectEntryPoint\n396: THEN it SHALL return entry point with Path \"/api\"\n397: \n398: // Scenario 2: selectEntryPoint no matching path returns first\n399: GIVEN entry points [{Path: \"/api\"}, {Path: \"/execute\"}] and invocationPath \"/other/path\"\n400: WHEN calling selectEntryPoint\n401: THEN it SHALL return first entry point as default\n402: \n403: // Scenario 3: selectEntryPoint empty entry points\n404: GIVEN empty entry points slice\n405: WHEN calling selectEntryPoint\n406: THEN it SHALL return nil\n407: \n408: // Scenario 4: buildTargetURL with protocol\n409: GIVEN entry point with Protocol \"http\" and Endpoint \"localhost:8080\"\n410: WHEN calling buildTargetURL\n411: THEN result SHALL be URL with Scheme \"http\" and Host \"localhost:8080\"\n412: \n413: // Scenario 5: buildTargetURL with endpoint containing protocol\n414: GIVEN entry point with empty Protocol and Endpoint \"http://localhost:9000\"\n415: WHEN calling buildTargetURL\n416: THEN result SHALL be URL with Scheme \"http\" and Host \"localhost:9000\"\n417: ```\n418: \n419: ---\n420: \n421: ### REQ-012: Reverse Proxy\n422: \n423: **GIVEN** requests need to be proxied to sandbox  \n424: **WHEN** implementing reverse proxy  \n425: **THEN** proper headers and response handling shall be implemented\n426: \n427: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n428: \n429: ```go\n430: // Scenario 1: ReverseProxyWrapper struct\n431: GIVEN pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go\n432: WHEN reading ReverseProxyWrapper struct\n433: THEN it SHALL contain director, modifyResponse, errorHandler function fields\n434: \n435: // Scenario 2: Director sets target URL\n436: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper Director function\n437: WHEN modifying request\n438: THEN req.URL.Scheme SHALL be set to target.Scheme\n439: AND req.URL.Host SHALL be set to target.Host\n440: AND req.URL.Path SHALL be set correctly\n441: \n442: // Scenario 3: Director sets forwarded headers\n443: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper Director function\n444: WHEN modifying request\n445: THEN X-Forwarded-Host header SHALL be set\n446: AND X-Forwarded-Proto header SHALL be set\n447: AND X-Forwarded-For header SHALL be set\n448: \n449: // Scenario 4: Director sets JWT Authorization\n450: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper with non-empty jwt parameter\n451: WHEN modifying request\n452: THEN Authorization header SHALL be \"Bearer \" + jwt\n453: \n454: // Scenario 5: ModifyResponse sets session header\n455: GIVEN ReverseProxyWrapper ModifyResponse function\n456: WHEN modifying response\n457: THEN x-agentcube-session-id header SHALL be set\n458: \n459: // Scenario 6: ErrorHandler connection refused\n460: GIVEN error message containing \"connection refused\"\n461: WHEN ErrorHandler handles error\n462: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 502 with JSON {\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"}\n463: \n464: // Scenario 7: ErrorHandler timeout\n465: GIVEN error message containing \"timeout\"\n466: WHEN ErrorHandler handles error\n467: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 504 with JSON {\"error\": \"sandbox timeout\"}\n468: ```\n469: \n470: ---\n471: \n472: ### REQ-013: JWT Manager\n473: \n474: **GIVEN** Router needs JWT token generation for sandbox authentication  \n475: **WHEN** implementing JWT management  \n476: **THEN** JWTManager shall generate RS256 signed tokens\n477: \n478: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n479: \n480: ```go\n481: // Scenario 1: JWTManager struct\n482: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n483: WHEN reading JWTManager struct\n484: THEN it SHALL contain privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey and publicKey *rsa.PublicKey fields\n485: \n486: // Scenario 2: NewJWTManager constructor\n487: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n488: WHEN calling NewJWTManager()\n489: THEN it SHALL generate RSA key with size 2048\n490: AND it SHALL return *JWTManager with keys initialized\n491: \n492: // Scenario 3: GenerateToken method\n493: GIVEN JWTManager instance\n494: WHEN calling GenerateToken(claims)\n495: THEN token SHALL use jwt.SigningMethodRS256\n496: AND token SHALL contain exp claim with 5 minute expiration\n497: AND token SHALL contain iat claim with current time\n498: AND token SHALL contain iss claim \"agentcube-router\"\n499: AND custom claims SHALL be added to token\n500: \n501: // Scenario 4: JWTSigningError on failure\n502: GIVEN JWTManager signing failure\n503: WHEN GenerateToken returns error\n504: THEN it SHALL return JWTSigningError wrapping the underlying error\n505: \n506: // Scenario 5: RSA constants\n507: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n508: WHEN reading constants\n509: THEN rsaKeySize SHALL be 2048\n510: AND jwtExpiration SHALL be 5 minutes\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ### REQ-014: Identity Namespace\n516: \n517: **GIVEN** Router needs configurable namespace  \n518: **WHEN** setting identity namespace  \n519: **THEN** it shall read from environment variable\n520: \n521: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n522: \n523: ```go\n524: // Scenario 1: IdentityNamespace default\n525: GIVEN AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE environment variable not set\n526: WHEN init() function executes\n527: THEN IdentityNamespace SHALL be \"default\"\n528: \n529: // Scenario 2: IdentityNamespace from environment\n530: GIVEN AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE environment variable set to \"my-namespace\"\n531: WHEN init() function executes\n532: THEN IdentityNamespace SHALL be \"my-namespace\"\n533: \n534: // Scenario 3: IdentitySecretName constant\n535: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n536: WHEN reading constants\n537: THEN IdentitySecretName SHALL be \"picod-router-identity\"\n538: \n539: // Scenario 4: Key data key constants\n540: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt.go\n541: WHEN reading constants\n542: THEN PrivateKeyDataKey SHALL be \"private.pem\"\n543: AND PublicKeyDataKey SHALL be \"public.pem\"\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ### REQ-015: Custom Error Types\n549: \n550: **GIVEN** Router needs unified error handling  \n551: **WHEN** defining error types  \n552: **THEN** all errors shall implement APIStatus interface\n553: \n554: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n555: \n556: ```go\n557: // Scenario 1: APIStatus interface\n558: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n559: WHEN reading APIStatus interface\n560: THEN it SHALL define Status() int\n561: AND it SHALL define Code() string\n562: AND it SHALL define Message() string\n563: \n564: // Scenario 2: SessionNotFoundError\n565: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n566: WHEN reading SessionNotFoundError struct\n567: THEN it SHALL contain SessionID string field\n568: AND Status() SHALL return 404\n569: AND Code() SHALL return \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n570: AND Message() SHALL return \"session not found\"\n571: \n572: // Scenario 3: SandboxUnreachableError\n573: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n574: WHEN reading SandboxUnreachableError struct\n575: THEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\n576: AND Status() SHALL return 502\n577: AND Code() SHALL return \"SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE\"\n578: \n579: // Scenario 4: SandboxTimeoutError\n580: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n581: WHEN reading SandboxTimeoutError struct\n582: THEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\n583: AND Status() SHALL return 504\n584: AND Code() SHALL return \"SANDBOX_TIMEOUT\"\n585: \n586: // Scenario 5: JWTSigningError\n587: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n588: WHEN reading JWTSigningError struct\n589: THEN it SHALL contain Err error field\n590: AND Status() SHALL return 500\n591: AND Code() SHALL return \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"\n592: \n593: // Scenario 6: ServerOverloadedError\n594: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n595: WHEN reading ServerOverloadedError struct\n596: THEN Status() SHALL return 429\n597: AND Code() SHALL return \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"\n598: \n599: // Scenario 7: NoEntryPointError\n600: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n601: WHEN reading NoEntryPointError struct\n602: THEN it SHALL contain SandboxID string field\n603: AND Status() SHALL return 404\n604: AND Code() SHALL return \"NO_ENTRY_POINT\"\n605: \n606: // Scenario 8: WorkloadManagerError\n607: GIVEN pkg/router/errors.go\n608: WHEN reading WorkloadManagerError struct\n609: THEN it SHALL contain StatusCode int and Msg string fields\n610: AND Code() SHALL return \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR\"\n611: ```\n612: \n613: ---\n614: \n615: ### REQ-016: Concurrency Limit Middleware\n616: \n617: **GIVEN** Router needs to limit concurrent requests  \n618: **WHEN** implementing concurrency middleware  \n619: **THEN** requests exceeding limit shall receive 429 response\n620: \n621: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n622: \n623: ```go\n624: // Scenario 1: concurrencyLimitMiddleware function\n625: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\n626: WHEN reading concurrencyLimitMiddleware function\n627: THEN it SHALL use semaphore channel for concurrency control\n628: \n629: // Scenario 2: Request allowed within limit\n630: GIVEN concurrency limit of 1000\n631: WHEN request arrives within limit\n632: THEN request SHALL proceed via c.Next()\n633: \n634: // Scenario 3: Request rejected over limit\n635: GIVEN concurrency limit exceeded\n636: WHEN request arrives\n637: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 429\n638: AND JSON body SHALL contain {\"error\": \"server overloaded, please try again later\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}\n639: AND c.Abort() SHALL be called\n640: \n641: // Scenario 4: Default limit when config invalid\n642: GIVEN maxConcurrent <= 0\n643: WHEN middleware initialized\n644: THEN limit SHALL be set to 1000\n645: ```\n646: \n647: ---\n648: \n649: ### REQ-017: Logging Middleware\n650: \n651: **GIVEN** requests need structured logging  \n652: **WHEN** implementing logging middleware  \n653: **THEN** request details shall be logged\n654: \n655: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n656: \n657: ```go\n658: // Scenario 1: loggingMiddleware function\n659: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\n660: WHEN reading loggingMiddleware function\n661: THEN it SHALL capture request start time\n662: AND it SHALL call c.Next() and then log\n663: \n664: // Scenario 2: Log fields captured\n665: GIVEN loggingMiddleware processing request\n666: WHEN request completes\n667: THEN logger.Info SHALL be called\n668: AND log SHALL contain method, path, status, duration fields\n669: \n670: // Scenario 3: Nil logger handled\n671: GIVEN loggingMiddleware with nil logger\n672: WHEN request completes\n673: THEN no logging SHALL occur\n674: ```\n675: \n676: ---\n677: \n678: ### REQ-018: Recovery Middleware\n679: \n680: **GIVEN** panics in handlers need recovery  \n681: **WHEN** implementing recovery middleware  \n682: **THEN** panics shall be caught and 500 response returned\n683: \n684: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n685: \n686: ```go\n687: // Scenario 1: recoveryMiddleware function\n688: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware.go\n689: WHEN reading recoveryMiddleware function\n690: THEN it SHALL use defer with recover()\n691: \n692: // Scenario 2: Panic recovered\n693: GIVEN handler panics\n694: WHEN recoveryMiddleware catches panic\n695: THEN logger.Error SHALL be called with error, path, method fields\n696: AND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with JSON {\"error\": \"internal server error\"}\n697: AND c.Abort() SHALL be called\n698: \n699: // Scenario 3: Nil logger handled\n700: GIVEN recoveryMiddleware with nil logger\n701: WHEN panic occurs\n702: THEN no logging SHALL occur\n703: AND HTTP 500 response SHALL still be returned\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ---\n707: \n708: ### REQ-019: Server Lifecycle\n709: \n710: **GIVEN** Server needs graceful startup and shutdown  \n711: **WHEN** managing server lifecycle  \n712: **THEN** Start and Stop methods shall be properly implemented\n713: \n714: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n715: \n716: ```go\n717: // Scenario 1: Start method without TLS\n718: GIVEN Server with EnableTLS false\n719: WHEN calling Start(ctx)\n720: THEN httpServer.ListenAndServe SHALL be called\n721: AND waitForShutdown SHALL be started in goroutine\n722: \n723: // Scenario 2: Start method with TLS\n724: GIVEN Server with EnableTLS true and valid TLSCert/TLSKey\n725: WHEN calling Start(ctx)\n726: THEN httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS SHALL be called\n727: \n728: // Scenario 3: TLS config validation\n729: GIVEN Server with EnableTLS true but missing TLSCert or TLSKey\n730: WHEN calling Start(ctx)\n731: THEN it SHALL return error \"TLS cert and key are required when EnableTLS is true\"\n732: \n733: // Scenario 4: waitForShutdown behavior\n734: GIVEN Server.Start called\n735: WHEN ctx.Done() channel closes\n736: THEN shutdownCtx SHALL be created with 10 second timeout\n737: AND httpServer.Shutdown SHALL be called\n738: \n739: // Scenario 5: Stop method\n740: GIVEN running Server\n741: WHEN calling Stop()\n742: THEN httpServer.Shutdown SHALL be called with 10 second timeout context\n743: ```\n744: \n745: ---\n746: \n747: ### REQ-020: Logger Interface\n748: \n749: **GIVEN** Router needs structured logging  \n750: **WHEN** defining logger abstraction  \n751: **THEN** Logger interface shall support Info, Error, Warning methods\n752: \n753: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n754: \n755: ```go\n756: // Scenario 1: Logger interface definition\n757: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n758: WHEN reading Logger interface\n759: THEN it SHALL define Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n760: AND it SHALL define Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n761: AND it SHALL define Warning(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n762: \n763: // Scenario 2: Logger used in Server\n764: GIVEN Server struct\n765: WHEN reading the implementation\n766: THEN logger field SHALL be of type Logger\n767: \n768: // Scenario 3: Logger used in middleware\n769: GIVEN loggingMiddleware and recoveryMiddleware\n770: WHEN logging events\n771: THEN Logger interface methods SHALL be used\n772: ```\n773: \n774: ---\n775: \n776: ### REQ-021: Error Handling in Server\n777: \n778: **GIVEN** Server needs unified error responses  \n779: **WHEN** handling errors in handlers  \n780: **THEN** handleGetSandboxError shall map errors to correct HTTP codes\n781: \n782: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n783: \n784: ```go\n785: // Scenario 1: Kubernetes NotFound error\n786: GIVEN apierrors.IsNotFound(err) true\n787: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n788: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 404\n789: \n790: // Scenario 2: APIStatus error\n791: GIVEN error implementing apierrors.APIStatus\n792: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n793: THEN HTTP status code SHALL be extracted from APIStatus\n794: AND message SHALL be extracted from APIStatus\n795: AND HTTP 500 message SHALL be \"internal server error\"\n796: \n797: // Scenario 3: Router APIStatus error\n798: GIVEN error implementing router.APIStatus\n799: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n800: THEN response SHALL use routerErr.Status() for HTTP code\n801: AND JSON SHALL contain error, code fields\n802: \n803: // Scenario 4: Unknown error\n804: GIVEN error not implementing APIStatus\n805: WHEN handleGetSandboxError called\n806: THEN response SHALL be HTTP 500 with {\"error\": \"internal server error\"}\n807: ```\n808: \n809: ---\n810: \n811: ### REQ-022: Unit Tests\n812: \n813: **GIVEN** implementation needs test coverage  \n814: **WHEN** verifying functionality  \n815: **THEN** unit tests shall cover all core components\n816: \n817: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n818: \n819: ```go\n820: // Scenario 1: session_manager tests\n821: GIVEN pkg/router/session_manager_test.go\n822: WHEN running tests\n823: THEN NewSessionManager tests SHALL verify WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL requirement\n824: AND GetSandboxBySession tests SHALL verify existing session lookup\n825: AND GetSandboxBySession tests SHALL verify session creation\n826: AND createSandbox tests SHALL verify endpoint selection\n827: AND tests SHALL verify error handling\n828: \n829: // Scenario 2: server tests\n830: GIVEN pkg/router/server_test.go\n831: WHEN running tests\n832: THEN NewServer tests SHALL verify constructor with various configs\n833: AND health endpoint tests SHALL verify /health/live and /health/ready\n834: AND route registration tests SHALL verify all routes present\n835: AND lifecycle tests SHALL verify Start/Stop/GracefulShutdown\n836: AND TLS tests SHALL verify TLS requirement validation\n837: \n838: // Scenario 3: errors tests\n839: GIVEN pkg/router/errors_test.go\n840: WHEN running tests\n841: THEN all error types SHALL have tests verifying Error(), Status(), Code(), Message()\n842: AND APIStatus interface compliance SHALL be tested\n843: \n844: // Scenario 4: reverse_proxy tests\n845: GIVEN pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go\n846: WHEN running tests\n847: THEN selectEntryPoint tests SHALL verify path matching\n848: AND buildTargetURL tests SHALL verify URL construction\n849: \n850: // Scenario 5: middleware tests\n851: GIVEN pkg/router/middleware_test.go\n852: WHEN running tests\n853: THEN concurrencyLimit tests SHALL verify limit enforcement\n854: AND logging tests SHALL verify log output\n855: AND recovery tests SHALL verify panic handling\n856: \n857: // Scenario 6: jwt tests\n858: GIVEN pkg/router/jwt_test.go\n859: WHEN running tests\n860: THEN NewJWTManager tests SHALL verify key generation\n861: AND GenerateToken tests SHALL verify token creation and claims\n862: \n863: // Scenario 7: config tests\n864: GIVEN pkg/router/config_test.go\n865: WHEN running tests\n866: THEN DefaultConfig tests SHALL verify default values\n867: ```\n868: \n869: ---\n870: \n871: ### REQ-023: Code Quality\n872: \n873: **GIVEN** code needs to meet quality standards  \n874: **WHEN** running linting and validation  \n875: **THEN** code shall pass go vet and build\n876: \n877: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n878: \n879: ```go\n880: // Scenario 1: go vet passes\n881: GIVEN pkg/router/\n882: WHEN running go vet ./pkg/router/...\n883: THEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n884: \n885: // Scenario 2: Build succeeds\n886: GIVEN pkg/router/\n887: WHEN running go build ./pkg/router/...\n888: THEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n889: \n890: // Scenario 3: Test coverage threshold\n891: GIVEN pkg/router/\n892: WHEN running go test -cover ./pkg/router/...\n893: THEN coverage SHALL be greater than 80%\n894: \n895: // Scenario 4: All tests pass\n896: GIVEN pkg/router/\n897: WHEN running go test ./pkg/router/...\n898: THEN all tests SHALL pass without failures\n899: ```\n900: \n901: ---\n902: \n903: ### REQ-024: Package Documentation\n904: \n905: **GIVEN** package needs documentation  \n906: **WHEN** organizing package structure  \n907: **THEN** proper documentation shall be present\n908: \n909: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n910: \n911: ```go\n912: // Scenario 1: doc.go file exists\n913: GIVEN pkg/router/\n914: WHEN listing files\n915: THEN doc.go SHALL exist\n916: \n917: // Scenario 2: Interfaces documented\n918: GIVEN pkg/router/doc.go\n919: WHEN reading the file\n920: THEN Store, Logger, SessionManager, JWTManagerInterface, APIStatus interfaces SHALL be defined\n921: ```\n922: \n923: ---\n924: \n925: ### REQ-025: SandboxInfo Types\n926: \n927: **GIVEN** Router uses sandbox info types  \n928: **WHEN** working with sandbox data  \n929: **THEN** types shall support all necessary fields\n930: \n931: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n932: \n933: ```go\n934: // Scenario 1: SandboxInfo struct\n935: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n936: WHEN reading SandboxInfo struct\n937: THEN it SHALL contain Kind, SandboxID, SandboxNamespace, SandboxName, Name, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, EntryPoints fields\n938: AND all fields SHALL have JSON tags\n939: \n940: // Scenario 2: SandboxEntryPoint struct\n941: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n942: WHEN reading SandboxEntryPoint struct\n943: THEN it SHALL contain Path, Protocol, Endpoint fields with JSON tags\n944: \n945: // Scenario 3: CreateSandboxRequest struct\n946: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n947: WHEN reading CreateSandboxRequest struct\n948: THEN it SHALL contain Kind, Name, Namespace fields with JSON tags\n949: AND Validate method SHALL validate all fields\n950: \n951: // Scenario 4: CreateSandboxResponse struct\n952: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n953: WHEN reading CreateSandboxResponse struct\n954: THEN it SHALL contain SessionID, SandboxID, SandboxName, EntryPoints fields with JSON tags\n955: \n956: // Scenario 5: Kind constants\n957: GIVEN pkg/common/types/sandbox.go\n958: WHEN reading constants\n959: THEN AgentRuntimeKind SHALL be \"AgentRuntime\"\n960: AND CodeInterpreterKind SHALL be \"CodeInterpreter\"\n961: AND SandboxKind SHALL be \"Sandbox\"\n962: AND SandboxClaimKind SHALL be \"SandboxClaim\"\n963: ```\n964: \n965: ---\n966: \n967: ## Implementation Files\n968: \n969: | File | Purpose |\n970: |------|---------|\n971: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager implementation with GetSandboxBySession and createSandbox |\n972: | `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTPServer implementation with Gin framework, routes, and lifecycle |\n973: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | ReverseProxyWrapper, selectEntryPoint, buildTargetURL |\n974: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | concurrencyLimitMiddleware, loggingMiddleware, recoveryMiddleware |\n975: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation and token signing |\n976: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Custom error types implementing APIStatus interface |\n977: | `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct and DefaultConfig function |\n978: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Interface definitions: Store, Logger, SessionManager, APIStatus |\n979: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | SessionManager unit tests |\n980: | `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server unit tests |\n981: | `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Reverse proxy and entry point tests |\n982: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n983: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT manager unit tests |\n984: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Error types unit tests |\n985: | `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Config unit tests |\n986: | `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` | SandboxInfo, SandboxEntryPoint, request/response types |\n987: \n988: ---\n989: \n990: ## Dependencies\n991: \n992: | Package | Purpose |\n993: |---------|---------|\n994: | `net/http` | HTTP server and client |\n995: | `context` | Request context for cancellation |\n996: | `time` | Time handling for sessions and timeouts |\n997: | `encoding/json` | JSON marshaling for requests/responses |\n998: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP router framework |\n999: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT token generation |\n1000: | `golang.org/x/net/http2` | HTTP2 transport support |\n1001: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Kubernetes error types |\n1002: \n1003: ---\n1004: \n1005: ## API Endpoints\n1006: \n1007: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n1008: |----------|--------|---------|\n1009: | `/health/live` | GET | Kubernetes liveness probe |\n1010: | `/health/ready` | GET | Kubernetes readiness probe |\n1011: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET, POST | AgentRuntime invocation proxy |\n1012: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET, POST | CodeInterpreter invocation proxy |\n1013: \n1014: ---\n1015: \n1016: ## Error Codes\n1017: \n1018: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n1019: |------|-------------|-------------|\n1020: | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Session ID not found in store |\n1021: | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | 404 | No entry point configured for sandbox |\n1022: | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | 502 | Sandbox endpoint connection refused |\n1023: | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | 504 | Sandbox endpoint timeout |\n1024: | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | 500 | JWT token signing failure |\n1025: | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | 429 | Concurrent request limit exceeded |\n1026: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR` | varies | Error from WorkloadManager |\n1027: \n1028: ---\n1029: \n1030: ## Validation Checklist\n1031: \n1032: - [ ] SessionManager correctly creates and retrieves sessions\n1033: - [ ] GetSandboxBySession handles existing sessions and creates new ones\n1034: - [ ] createSandbox sends correct requests to WorkloadManager\n1035: - [ ] Store interface supports session persistence\n1036: - [ ] Service account token correctly added to requests\n1037: - [ ] Server properly configured with Gin framework\n1038: - [ ] All routes registered with correct middleware\n1039: - [ ] Health endpoints respond correctly\n1040: - [ ] Invoke handlers route requests to sandbox entry points\n1041: - [ ] Entry point selection works correctly\n1042: - [ ] Reverse proxy sets proper headers\n1043: - [ ] JWTManager generates valid RS256 tokens\n1044: - [ ] All error types implement APIStatus interface\n1045: - [ ] Middleware enforces concurrency limit\n1046: - [ ] Logging middleware captures request details\n1047: - [ ] Recovery middleware handles panics\n1048: - [ ] Server lifecycle supports graceful shutdown\n1049: - [ ] Logger interface supports structured logging\n1050: - [ ] Error handling maps to correct HTTP codes\n1051: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n1052: - [ ] Build succeeds without errors\n1053: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n1054: - [ ] All tests pass without failures\n\n(End of file - total 1054 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\nModule: `pkg/router`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Router session management subsystem, providing session lifecycle management, sandbox routing, reverse proxy, JWT authentication, unified error handling, and middleware support for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter invocation requests.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: SessionManager Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the Router needs to manage sessions for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter  \n**WHEN** handling session-based routing requests  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857252980,"end":1775857253001}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775857253033,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d79573a8c001zLg8of1EVgjX6M","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79572a25001i15I4y4V3TnReq","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":26654,"input":516,"output":60,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":26078}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775857256671,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d795748dc001xrzQzELTq7Joiu","messageID":"msg_d79573ac00012G5dSsRmXvIWVB","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857350198,"sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","part":{"id":"prt_d7958b518001vQEUYyDJDS4O2r","messageID":"msg_d79573ac00012G5dSsRmXvIWVB","sessionID":"ses_286aa1d3dffe6vYami0G5lPSaL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7e858d60433b46acaf72f462803bd16d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-013: Redis Storage Implementation\n\nModule: `pkg/store`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement Redis-backed session storage for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Store Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the system needs to persist sandbox metadata  \n**WHEN** managing session storage  \n**THEN** Store interface shall be properly defined with all required methods\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Store interface definition\nGIVEN pkg/store/store.go\nWHEN reading the Store interface\nTHEN it SHALL define Ping(ctx context.Context) error\nAND it SHALL define GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\nAND it SHALL define StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\nAND it SHALL define UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\nAND it SHALL define DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\nAND it SHALL define ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\nAND it SHALL define ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\nAND it SHALL define UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\nAND it SHALL define Close() error\n\n// Scenario 2: ErrNotFound exported\nGIVEN pkg/store/store.go\nWHEN reading the error variable\nTHEN ErrNotFound SHALL be defined as errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Redis Store Type Constants\n\n**GIVEN** multiple backend providers need identification  \n**WHEN** selecting storage backend  \n**THEN** provider type constants shall be defined\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Redis store type constant\nGIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\nWHEN reading constants\nTHEN redisStoreType SHALL be \"redis\"\n\n// Scenario 2: Valkey store type constant\nGIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\nWHEN reading constants\nTHEN valkeyStoreType SHALL be \"valkey\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Singleton Access\n\n**GIVEN** single storage instance needed across application  \n**WHEN** accessing storage  \n**THEN** singleton pattern shall be implemented\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Storage function exists\nGIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\nWHEN reading the exported function\nTHEN Storage() SHALL return Store interface\n\n// Scenario 2: sync.Once used\nGIVEN pkg/store/singleton.go\nWHEN reading initialization logic\nTHEN initStoreOnce SHALL be of type *sync.Once\nAND provider SHALL be of type Store\n\n// Scenario 3: Single initialization\nGIVEN multiple goroutines calling Storage()\nWHEN they execute concurrently\nTHEN initStore SHALL execute exactly once via initStoreOnce.Do()\n\n// Scenario 4: Init failure is fatal\nGIVEN initialization error occurs\nWHEN initStore returns error\nTHEN klog.Fatalf SHALL be called with message \"init store failed: %v\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: Redis Client Initialization\n\n**GIVEN** Redis backend needs configuration  \n**WHEN** initializing Redis client  \n**THEN** environment variables shall be read correctly\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Redis address required\nGIVEN REDIS_ADDR environment variable set to \"localhost:6379\"\nWHEN makeRedisOptions() is called\nTHEN returned Options.Addr SHALL be \"localhost:6379\"\n\n// Scenario 2: Redis password passed\nGIVEN REDIS_PASSWORD environment variable set to \"secret\"\nWHEN makeRedisOptions() is called\nTHEN returned Options.Password SHALL be \"secret\"\n\n// Scenario 3: Password required by default\nGIVEN REDIS_ADDR set and REDIS_PASSWORD empty and REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED unset\nWHEN Redis store initializes\nTHEN initialization SHALL fail with password required error\n\n// Scenario 4: Password optional when disabled\nGIVEN REDIS_ADDR set and REDIS_PASSWORD empty and REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"\nWHEN Redis store initializes\nTHEN initialization SHALL succeed with empty password\n\n// Scenario 5: REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED case insensitive\nGIVEN REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"FALSE\"\nWHEN checking password requirement\nTHEN comparison SHALL be case-insensitive\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Redis Store Struct\n\n**GIVEN** Redis implementation needs state  \n**WHEN** defining redisStore struct  \n**THEN** required fields shall be present\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: redisStore struct definition\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_redis.go\nWHEN reading the struct\nTHEN redisStore SHALL contain cli *redisv9.Client\nAND redisStore SHALL contain sessionPrefix string\nAND redisStore SHALL contain expiryIndexKey string\nAND redisStore SHALL contain lastActivityIndexKey string\n\n// Scenario 2: sessionPrefix value\nGIVEN redisStore instance\nWHEN initialized\nTHEN sessionPrefix SHALL be \"session:\"\n\n// Scenario 3: expiryIndexKey value\nGIVEN redisStore instance\nWHEN initialized\nTHEN expiryIndexKey SHALL be \"session:expiry\"\n\n// Scenario 4: lastActivityIndexKey value\nGIVEN redisStore instance\nWHEN initialized\nTHEN lastActivityIndexKey SHALL be \"session:last_activity\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Key Naming Convention\n\n**GIVEN** session data needs consistent key format  \n**WHEN** constructing Redis keys  \n**THEN** prefix pattern shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: sessionKey function\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_redis.go\nWHEN reading sessionKey function\nTHEN it SHALL return sessionPrefix + sessionID\n\n// Scenario 2: Session key format\nGIVEN session ID \"abc123\"\nWHEN sessionKey(\"abc123\") is called\nTHEN result SHALL be \"session:abc123\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: Ping Connectivity\n\n**GIVEN** connectivity verification needed  \n**WHEN** calling Ping  \n**THEN** Redis PING command shall be issued\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Ping returns nil on success\nGIVEN connected Redis client\nWHEN Ping(ctx) is called\nTHEN Redis PING command SHALL be issued\nAND return SHALL be nil when response equals \"PONG\"\n\n// Scenario 2: Ping returns error on failure\nGIVEN unreachable Redis server\nWHEN Ping(ctx) is called\nTHEN error from Redis client SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: Get Sandbox By Session ID\n\n**GIVEN** session lookup needed  \n**WHEN** calling GetSandboxBySessionID  \n**THEN** correct Redis GET shall be issued\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Get existing session\nGIVEN key \"session:abc\" exists with valid JSON\nWHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\nTHEN Redis GET session:abc SHALL be issued\nAND returned *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be unmarshaled from JSON\n\n// Scenario 2: Get missing session\nGIVEN no key \"session:xyz\"\nWHEN GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\") is called\nTHEN redis.Nil error SHALL be detected\nAND method SHALL return nil, ErrNotFound\n\n// Scenario 3: JSON unmarshal error handled\nGIVEN key \"session:abc\" with invalid JSON\nWHEN GetSandboxBySessionID is called\nTHEN unmarshal error SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Store Sandbox Atomically\n\n**GIVEN** new session creation needed  \n**WHEN** calling StoreSandbox  \n**THEN** atomic pipeline shall execute\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Reject nil sandbox\nGIVEN nil sandbox parameter\nWHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, nil) is called\nTHEN error SHALL be returned indicating sandbox is nil\n\n// Scenario 2: Reject zero expiry\nGIVEN sandbox with ExpiresAt being zero time.Time{}\nWHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\nTHEN error SHALL be returned indicating invalid expiry\n\n// Scenario 3: Pipeline executes SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD activity\nGIVEN valid sandbox with SessionID \"s1\" and ExpiresAt t\nWHEN StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\nTHEN pipeline SHALL execute SETNX session:s1 <json>\nAND pipeline SHALL execute ZADD session:expiry <t.Unix()> s1\nAND pipeline SHALL execute ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> s1\nAND return SHALL be nil on success\n\n// Scenario 4: Reject duplicate session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" already exists\nWHEN StoreSandbox for same session ID is called\nTHEN SETNX SHALL return false\nAND error SHALL indicate session already exists\n\n// Scenario 5: Pipeline failure returns error\nGIVEN any command in pipeline fails\nWHEN StoreSandbox processes pipeline\nTHEN error SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-010: Update Sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** session data update needed  \n**WHEN** calling UpdateSandbox  \n**THEN** SET with XX shall be issued\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Update existing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\nWHEN UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\nTHEN Redis SET session:s1 <json> XX SHALL be issued\nAND return SHALL be nil on success\n\n// Scenario 2: Update missing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\nWHEN UpdateSandbox is called\nTHEN SET with XX SHALL return false\nAND error SHALL indicate key does not exist\n\n// Scenario 3: Indexes not modified\nGIVEN UpdateSandbox called\nWHEN executing the method\nTHEN expiry ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\nAND last_activity ZSET SHALL NOT be modified\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-011: Delete Sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** session removal needed  \n**WHEN** calling DeleteSandboxBySessionID  \n**THEN** atomic cleanup shall execute\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Delete existing session atomically\nGIVEN session \"s1\" exists with ZSET entries\nWHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\nTHEN pipeline SHALL execute DEL session:s1\nAND pipeline SHALL execute ZREM session:expiry s1\nAND pipeline SHALL execute ZREM session:last_activity s1\nAND return SHALL be nil\n\n// Scenario 2: Delete missing session succeeds\nGIVEN session \"s1\" does not exist\nWHEN DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"s1\") is called\nTHEN pipeline SHALL still execute DEL and ZREM\nAND return SHALL be nil (no error for missing)\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-012: List Expired Sandboxes\n\n**GIVEN** expiry-based cleanup needed  \n**WHEN** calling ListExpiredSandboxes  \n**THEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Zero limit returns nil\nGIVEN limit <= 0\nWHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\nTHEN return SHALL be nil, nil without Redis calls\n\n// Scenario 2: ZRANGEBYSCORE with limit\nGIVEN ZSET session:expiry contains entries\nAND before = 2025-01-01T00:00:00Z\nAND limit = 10\nWHEN ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\nTHEN ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf <before.Unix()> LIMIT 0 10 SHALL be issued\n\n// Scenario 3: Pipeline GET for each session ID\nGIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs\nWHEN loading sandbox data\nTHEN pipeline GET session:{id} SHALL be issued for each ID\nAND slice of *types.SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n\n// Scenario 4: Skip orphan ZSET entries\nGIVEN session ID \"orphan1\" in expiry ZSET but no session:orphan1 key\nWHEN loading sandbox data\nTHEN orphan entry SHALL be skipped without error\nAND other valid sessions SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-013: List Inactive Sandboxes\n\n**GIVEN** activity-based cleanup needed  \n**WHEN** calling ListInactiveSandboxes  \n**THEN** activity index shall be queried\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: ZRANGEBYSCORE on activity index\nGIVEN ZSET session:last_activity contains entries\nAND before and limit are valid\nWHEN ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\nTHEN ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf <before.Unix()> LIMIT 0 limit SHALL be issued\n\n// Scenario 2: Session data loaded via pipeline\nGIVEN ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session IDs\nWHEN processing results\nTHEN session data SHALL be loaded via pipeline GETs\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-014: Update Session Last Activity\n\n**GIVEN** activity timestamp update needed  \n**WHEN** calling UpdateSessionLastActivity  \n**THEN** existence check shall precede ZADD\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Reject empty session ID\nGIVEN empty sessionID string\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at) is called\nTHEN error SHALL indicate session ID is empty\n\n// Scenario 2: Use current time when at is zero\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\nAND at is zero time.Time{}\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\nTHEN time.Now() SHALL be used for the score\n\n// Scenario 3: Update activity for existing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" exists\nAND at is non-zero time\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\nTHEN ZADD session:last_activity <at.Unix()> s1 SHALL be issued\nAND return SHALL be nil\n\n// Scenario 4: Reject missing session\nGIVEN key \"session:s1\" does not exist\nWHEN UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"s1\", at) is called\nTHEN ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-015: Close Connection\n\n**GIVEN** graceful shutdown needed  \n**WHEN** calling Close  \n**THEN** Redis client shall be closed\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Close succeeds\nGIVEN connected Redis client\nWHEN Close() is called\nTHEN cli.Close() SHALL be invoked\nAND return SHALL be nil\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-016: Store Type Selection\n\n**GIVEN** multiple backend options  \n**WHEN** initializing store  \n**THEN** correct backend shall be selected\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Default to redis\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE not set\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN Redis implementation SHALL be selected\n\n// Scenario 2: Explicit redis\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"redis\"\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN Redis implementation SHALL be selected\n\n// Scenario 3: Case-insensitive store type\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"REDIS\"\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN Redis implementation SHALL be selected\n\n// Scenario 4: Invalid store type\nGIVEN STORE_TYPE = \"unknown\"\nWHEN initStore runs\nTHEN initialization SHALL fail with error\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-017: SandboxInfo JSON Marshaling\n\n**GIVEN** sandbox data serialized as JSON  \n**WHEN** marshaling/unmarshaling  \n**THEN** correct field mapping shall be used\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: SandboxInfo JSON fields\nGIVEN types.SandboxInfo struct\nWHEN marshaled to JSON\nTHEN Kind SHALL map to \"kind\"\nAND SandboxID SHALL map to \"sandboxId\"\nAND SandboxNamespace SHALL map to \"sandboxNamespace\"\nAND Name SHALL map to \"name\"\nAND EntryPoints SHALL map to \"entryPoints\"\nAND SessionID SHALL map to \"sessionId\"\nAND CreatedAt SHALL map to \"createdAt\"\nAND ExpiresAt SHALL map to \"expiresAt\"\nAND Status SHALL map to \"status\"\n\n// Scenario 2: SandboxEntryPoint JSON fields\nGIVEN types.SandboxEntryPoint struct\nWHEN marshaled to JSON\nTHEN Path SHALL map to \"path\"\nAND Protocol SHALL map to \"protocol\"\nAND Endpoint SHALL map to \"endpoint\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-018: Unit Tests\n\n**GIVEN** implementation needs test coverage  \n**WHEN** verifying functionality  \n**THEN** unit tests shall cover all core components\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: Store interface tests\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN ErrNotFound tests SHALL verify error message\nAND interface compliance SHALL be tested\n\n// Scenario 2: Redis store tests\nGIVEN pkg/store/store_redis_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN Ping tests SHALL verify connectivity\nAND GetSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify lookup and not found\nAND StoreSandbox tests SHALL verify atomic creation and validation\nAND UpdateSandbox tests SHALL verify update semantics\nAND DeleteSandboxBySessionID tests SHALL verify cleanup\nAND ListExpiredSandboxes tests SHALL verify expiry query\nAND ListInactiveSandboxes tests SHALL verify activity query\nAND UpdateSessionLastActivity tests SHALL verify activity update\n\n// Scenario 3: Singleton tests\nGIVEN pkg/store/singleton_test.go\nWHEN running tests\nTHEN Storage() tests SHALL verify singleton behavior\nAND concurrent access SHALL be tested\nAND store type selection SHALL be tested\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-019: Code Quality\n\n**GIVEN** code needs to meet quality standards  \n**WHEN** running linting and validation  \n**THEN** code shall pass go vet and build\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: go vet passes\nGIVEN pkg/store/\nWHEN running go vet ./pkg/store/...\nTHEN zero issues SHALL be reported\n\n// Scenario 2: Build succeeds\nGIVEN pkg/store/\nWHEN running go build ./pkg/store/...\nTHEN build SHALL succeed without errors\n\n// Scenario 3: All tests pass\nGIVEN pkg/store/\nWHEN running go test ./pkg/store/...\nTHEN all tests SHALL pass without failures\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface and ErrNotFound error |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation with all methods |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Storage() singleton access and initStore |\n| `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Interface tests |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` | Redis implementation tests |\n| `pkg/store/singleton_test.go` | Singleton tests |\n| `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` | SandboxInfo and SandboxEntryPoint types |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo types |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging |\n| `context` | Request context |\n| `time` | Timestamp handling |\n| `sync` | Singleton initialization |\n\n---\n\n## Redis Operations Summary\n\n| Method | Redis Commands |\n|--------|----------------|\n| `Ping` | `PING` → expect `PONG` |\n| `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n| `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n| `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n\n---\n\n## ZSET Score Semantics\n\n| Index Key | Score Value | Member |\n|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| `session:expiry` | `ExpiresAt.Unix()` | session ID |\n| `session:last_activity` | `time.Now().Unix()` on store, `at.Unix()` on update | session ID |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|--------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes (unless disabled) | - | Case-insensitive check for \"false\" |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | - | Set to \"false\" to disable password |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Case-insensitive |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Store interface defined with all 9 methods\n- [ ] ErrNotFound exported with correct message\n- [ ] Redis store type constants defined\n- [ ] Singleton pattern correctly implemented\n- [ ] Redis client initialized from environment\n- [ ] Key naming uses \"session:\" prefix\n- [ ] Ping verifies connectivity\n- [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID handles found/not found\n- [ ] StoreSandbox validates input and uses atomic pipeline\n- [ ] UpdateSandbox uses SET XX semantics\n- [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleans all indexes\n- [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries expiry ZSET\n- [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries activity ZSET\n- [ ] UpdateSessionLastActivity checks existence\n- [ ] Close gracefully shuts down client\n- [ ] Store type selection works correctly\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Build succeeds without errors\n- [ ] All tests pass","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857349988,"end":1775857350194}}}}
